Privacy-protected contact tracking is a well-established concept, with a large amount of published research dating back to at least 2013.
However, PEPP-PT is a coordinated effort containing both centralised and decentralised approaches and is not a single protocol.Decentralised protocols include decentralised proximity tracking for preserving privacy (DP-PPT/DP-3T), temporary contact numbers (TCNs, formerly known as contact event numbers, CEN) and protocols and mechanisms for mobile contact tracking for privacy protection (PACT), among others.
In these protocols, the personally identifiable data never leaves the device and all matching occurs on the device.
The MIT Media Lab Privacy Group has been developing SafePaths, a platform for using privacy-protecting techniques by collecting and using location or route intersection data to track the spread of COVID-19.
