A phase I or II trial performs preliminary safety and immunogenicity tests, usually randomized, placebo-controlled and multi-site, while determining more accurate and effective doses.
Phase III trials usually involve more participants, including a control group, and evaluate the effectiveness of the vaccine in preventing disease, while controlling for adverse effects that occur at the optimal dose.
